.TH "platform_restore_cleanup" 9 "platform_restore_cleanup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_restore_cleanup \- Switch to the working state after failing restore.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" platform_restore_cleanup
.BI "(int platform_mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "platform_mode" 12
Whether or not to use the platform driver.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Use the platform driver to switch the system to the normal mode of operation
after a failing restore.

If \fBplatform_pre_restore\fP has been called before the failing restore, this
function must be called too, regardless of the result of
\fBplatform_pre_restore\fP.
